"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-07-30-paris-2024-olympics-super-falcons-must-fight-hard-to-beat-japan-oshoala\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Super Falcons forward, Asisat Oshoala has rallied her teammates ahead of Wednesday's crucial clash against Japan.  Randy Waldrum's side will be up against the Nadeshiko in their last group game at the Stade de la Beaujoire, Nantes.  The Super Falcons lost their opening two games to Brazil and Spain.  The West Africans must beat the Asian champions to have any chance of making it to the quarter-finals.  Oshoala declared that they must give their best to get a favourable result against the Japanese.  \\\"We just have to go all out against Japan. We have to go all out and give everything and make the best out of it because we still have the opportunity to qualify. Hope is not lost,\\\" the Bay FC forward said ahead of the game.  The encounter will kick-off at 4pm Nigeria time.  Transfer: LaLiga club, Sevilla give Iheanacho two-year contract  LaLiga: Complete player - Roberto Carlos hails Real Madrid star  2026 WAFCON: 'It would not happen for other tournaments' - Super Falcons' Plumptre slams CAF  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons Ajibade disappointed with postponement  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons decamped after postponement  Friendly: Cameroon coach gives reason for defeat to Super Falcons  Friendly: Babajide relishes Super Falcons' win over Cameroon  Friendly: Super Falcons floor Cameroon 3-1 in Yaounde  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"